A man was found early Friday on a St. Paul sidewalk after being fatally shot, authorities said. Officers responding to the 600 block of N. Dale Street about 3:10 a.m. saw the man down in front of a business, police said. Emergency responders declared him dead at the scene. Police said he was in his 50s. His identity has not been released. No arrests have been made. While police have yet to address a motive, they did say the killing does not appear to be random. Anyone with information about the city's 22nd homicide so far this year is urged to call police at 651-266-5650. 